quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
6,111,"Even if We had sent angels down to them and the dead had spoken to them, and even if We had assembled before them all the things, face to face, they would still not believe unless it be Allah's will that they believe. {1} Most of them behave in utter ignorance.",footnotes:1:The people under discussion are so perverse that they do not prefer to embrace the Truth in preference to falsehood by rightly exercising their choice and volition. The only way that is left for them to become lovers of the Truth is
6,112,"And so it is that against every Prophet We have set up the evil ones from among men and jinn, some of them inspire others with specious speech only by way of. delusion. {1} Had it been your Lord's will, they would not have done it. {2} Leave them alone to fabricate what they will.",footnotes:1:The Prophet (peace be on him) is told that he should not be unnerved even if the evil ones among both mankind and the jinn stood united against him and opposed him with all their might. For this was not the first time that such a thing had happened. Whenever a Prophet came and tried to lead people to the Truth
6,113,"So that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Life to Come might incline towards this attractive delusion, and that they may be well pleased with it and might acquire the evils that they are bent on acquiring."
6,114,"Shall I look upon anyone apart from Allah for judgement when it is He Who has revealed to you the Book in detail? {1} And those whom We gave the Book (before you) know that this (Book) has been revealed in truth by your Lord. Do not, then, be among the doubters. {2}",footnotes:1:The implied speaker in this sentence is the Prophet (peace be on him) and the words are addressed to the Muslims. The purpose of the sentence is to impress upon the Muslims that God has elucidated the relevant truths
6,115,"The Word of your Lord is perfect in truthfulness and justice; no one can change His words. He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing."
6,116,"(O Muhammad!) If you obey the majority of those who live on earth, they will lead you away from Allah's path. They only follow idle fancies, indulging in conjecture. {1}",footnotes:1:One need not follow the way of life of the majority
6,117,"And your - Lord knows well who stray from His path, and also those who are rightly-guided."
6,118,"If you believe in the signs of Allah, eat (the flesh) of that over which Allah's name has been pronounced. {1}",footnotes:1:Many nations have imposed on themselves superfluous religious taboos
